        <mxCell id="0HZxUmu4RZ-0vbJsPey3-8" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Summary&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;1. AWS Glue ingest data periodically(daily/weekly) by calling REST API to HDB Portal and upload the data into S3 bucket (new data in new folder, folder name = date).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;2. Once the source file uploaded, AWS Redshift load S3 new data(in today folder) , do transformation and merge (insert new / update existing data) into datawarehouse (ETL&amp;nbsp; pipeline)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;3. AWS Athena will do query/analysis AWS Redshit aggregate data as required in Tableau dashboard.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;4. Tableau will connect to AWS Athena, call the query and refresh the dashboard from time to time&lt;/p&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="190" width="560" x="80" y="470" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
